{{Chinese name|Lee}}
'''Lee Sze Ming''' ({{lang-zh|<U+674E><U+601D><U+660E>}}; born [[February 5]] [[1979]] in [[Hong Kong]]) is a [[Hong Kong]] [[football (soccer)|football]] player who currently plays for [[Eastern AA|Eastern]] (loan from [[Convoy Sun Hei]]). He can play in varies of positions (all attacking positisions), mostly as a forward and right wing. He scored for [[Hong Kong national football team|Hong Kong]] against [[Brazil national football team|Brazil]] in the [[2005 Carlsberg Cup]]. <ref>[http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=qqFY4_UfH1A Lee Sze Ming's goal - Hong Kong 1:7 Brazil], [[YouTube]]</ref>

Lee also plays for the [[Hong Kong national football team|Hong Kong]] 5-on-side team. Fans in Hong Kong often call him the ''King of 5-on-side''.

